[--name] <string>  Name of the guest instance
[--memory] <string>       Configure guest memory allocation. Ex:
[--vcpus] <string>         Number of vcpus to configure for your guest. Ex:
[--disk] <string>           Specify storage with various options. Ex.
[--cdrom] <string>         CD-ROM installation media
--cpu <string>             CPU model and features. Ex:
--metadata <string>   Configure guest metadata. Ex:
--location <string> LOCATION
--pxe                 Boot from the network using the PXE protocol
--import              Build guest around an existing disk image
--livecd              Treat the CD-ROM media as a Live CD
--extra-args <string> EXTRA_ARGS
--initrd-inject <string> INITRD_INJECT
--os-variant <string> DISTRO_VARIANT
--boot <string> BOOT           Configure guest boot settings. Ex:
--idmap <string>         Enable user namespace for LXC container. Ex:
--network <string> NETWORK
--graphics <string>   Configure guest display settings. Ex:
--controller <string> CONTROLLER
--input <string>         Configure a guest input device. Ex:
--serial <string>       Configure a guest serial device
--parallel <string>   Configure a guest parallel device
--channel <string>     Configure a guest communication channel
--console <string>     Configure a text console connection between the guest
--hostdev <string>     Configure physical USB/PCI/etc host devices to be
--filesystem <string> FILESYSTEM
--sound <string>       Configure guest sound device emulation
--watchdog <string>   Configure a guest watchdog device
--video <string>         Configure guest video hardware.
--smartcard <string> SMARTCARD
--redirdev <string>   Configure a guest redirection device. Ex:
--memballoon <string> MEMBALLOON
--tpm <string>             Configure a guest TPM device. Ex:
--rng <string>             Configure a guest RNG device. Ex:
--panic <string>         Configure a guest panic device. Ex:
--memdev <string>       Configure a guest memory device. Ex:
--security <string>   Set domain security driver configuration.
--cputune <string>     Tune CPU parameters for the domain process.
--numatune <string>   Tune NUMA policy for the domain process.
--memtune <string>     Tune memory policy for the domain process.
--blkiotune <string> BLKIOTUNE
--memorybacking <string> MEMORYBACKING
--features <string>   Set domain <features> XML. Ex:
--clock <string>         Set domain <clock> XML. Ex:
--pm <string>               Configure VM power management features
--events <string>       Configure VM lifecycle management policy
--resource <string>   Configure VM resource partitioning (cgroups)
--sysinfo <string>     Configure SMBIOS System Information. Ex:
--qemu-commandline <string> QEMU_COMMANDLINE
--hvm             This guest should be a fully virtualized guest
--paravirt        This guest should be a paravirtualized guest
--container           This guest should be a container guest
--virt-type HV_TYPE   Hypervisor name to use (kvm, qemu, xen, ...)
--arch ARCH           The CPU architecture to simulate
--machine MACHINE     The machine type to emulate
--autostart           Have domain autostart on host boot up.
--transient           Create a transient domain.
--wait WAIT           Minutes to wait for install to complete.
--noautoconsole       Don't automatically try to connect to the guest
--noreboot            Don't boot guest after completing install.
--dry-run             Run through install process, but do not create devices
--check <string>         Enable or disable validation checks. Example:

